     <td class="lower">		 
	 <p class="style1"><span class="style21">The Social Security Administration (SSA) has announced changes to the way Social Security Numbes (SSNs) are issued.  </span>     
	 <p class="style1"><span class="style21">Beginning June 25, 2011, all newly-issued SSNs will be randomized. The SSA is implementing the new randomized method to help protect the integrity of the SSN and extend the longevity of the nine-digit SSN nationwide.</span>     
	 <p class="style25">LexisNexis&reg; is working diligently to implement product modifications associated with this change. Adjustments to handle randomized SSNs will be made available prior to the Social Security Administration's implementation June 25, 2011.</p>
	 <p class="style25"><a href="http://www.lexisnexis.com/risk/ssa/" target="_blank">Click here</a> to learn about product specific changes.  </p>
